Belle, Megawide, Rizal Commercial: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-02-18T00:37:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/belle-megawide-rizal-commercial-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and prices are as of noon in Manila
yesterday.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1.4 percent to
3,866.38.    Belle Corp . (BEL PM): The property developer which plans to
open a Manila casino in December posted a 465.5 million peso
profit last year, a stock exchange filing showed without giving
a comparative figure. Belle reported a 385.9 million peso net
income in 2009, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. The
stock increased 3.5 percent to 5.10 pesos.  Megawide Corp. (MWIDE PM): The Philippine construction
company will start trading today after holding a 2.29 billion
peso initial public offering earlier this month. The company
sold 292 million shares at 7.84 pesos each.    Rizal Commercial Banking Corp . (RCB PM): The lender expects
to raise as much as 6.5 billion pesos from a planned share sale
within the first quarter, President Lorenzo Tan said. The bank
expects profit to rise this 10 percent this year and aim to grow
its loans by 15 percent, he also said. The stock advanced 2.7
percent to 26.65 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in  Manila  at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  